"{\"uid\": \"greekreporter.com-2024-02-23-aristotle-onassis-olympic-airways-plane-displayed-athens\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The beloved plane of the late Greek tycoon Aristotle Onassis, an Olympic Airways Boeing 747, was recently moved to a permanent place at Hellinikon, the former airport of Athens now being transformed into the largest metropolitan park inGreece.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 25, \"end\": 35, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Late_Greek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"late Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Late_Greek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Late_Greek\"}, {\"begin\": 43, \"end\": 60, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle_Onassis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aristotle Onassis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle_Onassis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle_Onassis\"}, {\"begin\": 65, \"end\": 80, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.054803502542095e-61, \"text\": \"Olympic Airways\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\"}, {\"begin\": 81, \"end\": 91, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_747\", \"score\": 0.9999999980518623, \"rank\": 1.9480054300389357e-09, \"text\": \"Boeing 747\", \"types\": [\"Q11436\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_747\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_747\"}, {\"begin\": 136, \"end\": 146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elliniko\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hellinikon\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elliniko\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elliniko\"}, {\"begin\": 170, \"end\": 176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.5992103410664278e-12, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier in the week, the \\\"OLYMPIC EAGLE\\\" (SX-OAB) was moved next to the main building of the old Athens Airport (referred to as the East Terminal) created by the world-renowned Finnish-born American architect Eero Saarinen.\", \"from\": 245, \"to\": 468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 435, \"end\": 443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Airlines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6781174022387187e-18, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Airlines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Airlines\"}, {\"begin\": 454, \"end\": 467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eero_Saarinen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eero Saarinen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q42973\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eero_Saarinen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eero_Saarinen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He had already gained international recognition for the original and elegant expressionism of the TWA passenger terminal in New York and the Dulles International Airport near Washington, DC.\", \"from\": 470, \"to\": 660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 568, \"end\": 571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trans_World_Airlines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.911879814403266e-19, \"text\": \"TWA\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trans_World_Airlines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trans_World_Airlines\"}, {\"begin\": 594, \"end\": 602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999898436727, \"rank\": 9.340219067500709e-09, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Saarinen building was inaugurated in 1969, the same year that Aristotle Onassis placed the order with Boeing for this aircraft.\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 793, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 728, \"end\": 745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle_Onassis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aristotle Onassis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle_Onassis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aristotle_Onassis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is also the reason why we called it \\\"The Airplane of Aristotle Onassis.\\\"\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 871, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lamda Development, the developers of Hellinikon, honored an agreement signed in May 2023 with the Cultural Center of Olympic Aviation Employees to showcase the historic aircraft.\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 1051, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 910, \"end\": 920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elliniko\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hellinikon\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elliniko\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elliniko\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In July 1956, the Greek State signed an agreement withOnassis, for the exclusive use of air transport in Greece.\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1165, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1071, \"end\": 1076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.999956122711801, \"rank\": 4.348417898119554e-05, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1158, \"end\": 1164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.995182448602758, \"rank\": 0.004840870465248483, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On April 6, 1957, the company was renamed Olympic Airways.\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1208, \"end\": 1223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.054803502542095e-61, \"text\": \"Olympic Airways\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first domestic flight started the same year.\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1273, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Generally, Olympic had an upswing on a domestic and international level, as well.\", \"from\": 1274, \"to\": 1355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, in 1971, a subsidiary airline, Olympic Aviation, was established to serve theGreek islandsmore economically and efficiently, and flights were expanded globally.\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1401, \"end\": 1417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Aviation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympic Aviation\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Aviation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Aviation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1972, Olympic turned to the important Greece-Australia market, beginning Boeing 707-320 operations between Athens and Sydney twice a week via Bangkok and Singapore.\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1699, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1608, \"end\": 1622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_707\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Boeing 707-320\", \"types\": [\"Q11436\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_707\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_707\"}, {\"begin\": 1642, \"end\": 1648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.5992103410664278e-12, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\"}, {\"begin\": 1653, \"end\": 1659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney_Airport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.357951622276899e-15, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney_Airport\"}, {\"begin\": 1677, \"end\": 1684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suvarnabhumi_Airport\", \"score\": 0.6773174494818278, \"rank\": 0.4764125754699744, \"text\": \"Bangkok\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suvarnabhumi_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suvarnabhumi_Airport\"}, {\"begin\": 1689, \"end\": 1698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Changi_Airport\", \"score\": 0.9999999999931788, \"rank\": 6.66915028396899e-12, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Changi_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Changi_Airport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1973, the death of Onassis' son, Alexander, in a plane crash shocked Greek people, and a new phase began for Olympic Airways.\", \"from\": 1701, \"to\": 1829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1737, \"end\": 1746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"score\": 0.999477287088193, \"rank\": 0.0004385945535933168, \"text\": \"Alexander\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\"}, {\"begin\": 1773, \"end\": 1785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999953583909194, \"rank\": 4.641630648969991e-06, \"text\": \"Greek people\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1813, \"end\": 1828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.054803502542095e-61, \"text\": \"Olympic Airways\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A few months later, Onassis sold all of the OA shares to the Greek state and died in 1975.\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1874, \"end\": 1876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_Australia\", \"score\": 0.9996434626468372, \"rank\": 0.00033072519734994414, \"text\": \"OA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1891, \"end\": 1896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.999956122711801, \"rank\": 4.348417898119554e-05, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The year of 1976 was a landmark year in the history of Olympic.\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 1985, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The airline passed into Greek government's dominance.\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 2039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2010, \"end\": 2015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.999956122711801, \"rank\": 4.348417898119554e-05, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The same year, the firm obtained the first Boeing 737-200 and created Olympic Catering.\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2083, \"end\": 2097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_737\", \"score\": 0.9999999978103915, \"rank\": 2.1894367832637114e-09, \"text\": \"Boeing 737-200\", \"types\": [\"Q11436\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_737\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing_737\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Twenty-five aircraft and thirty international destinations were served.\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2199, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From December 1977 until January 1978, there was the biggest strike ever in the history of Olympic, lasting thirty-five days.\", \"from\": 2201, \"to\": 2326, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The main reasons for the strike were the creation of labor regulations, crew composition, and new wage.\", \"from\": 2327, \"to\": 2430, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This prolonged strike had a pleasant end for employees.\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2486, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The beginning of the 1980s found Olympic facing more strikes, which sought to implement regulation flights and improve economic earnings.\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2625, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1982, the airline celebrated twenty-five years of operation.\", \"from\": 2626, \"to\": 2689, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the early 1990s, the staff had picked up Sundays, holidays, and night itineraries.\", \"from\": 2691, \"to\": 2776, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However on October 4th, bloody incidents unfolded between strikers and redundant and riot police outside the building of Olympic Catering.\", \"from\": 2777, \"to\": 2915, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On March 28, 2001, the airline made its last flight, from the Hellinikon airport for Thessaloniki.\", \"from\": 2917, \"to\": 3015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3002, \"end\": 3014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thessaloniki_Airport\", \"score\": 0.9999924156846857, \"rank\": 7.584334674477673e-06, \"text\": \"Thessaloniki\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thessaloniki_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thessaloniki_Airport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On December 31, 2009, Olympic Airlines ceased all operations, as flights toGreek islandshad already been allocated and were being flown by other carriers.\", \"from\": 3017, \"to\": 3171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3039, \"end\": 3055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympic Airlines\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Airlines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Flights to destinations outside of the European Union had been allocated to other carriers, which began operating them from January 1, 2010.\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3220, \"end\": 3225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999976684194, \"rank\": 2.331160832001179e-08, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"See all thelatest newsfrom Greece and the world atGreekreporter.com.Contact our newsroomto report an update or send your story, photos and videos.\", \"from\": 3314, \"to\": 3460, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3341, \"end\": 3347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.995182448602758, \"rank\": 0.004840870465248483, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow GR onGoogle Newsandsubscribe hereto our daily email!\", \"from\": 3461, \"to\": 3520, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 Copyright - GreekReporter.com\", \"from\": 3522, \"to\": 3553, \"entities\": []}]}"